  "text": "For preparing whole cell lysates, bacterial cells were disrupted by sonication using 5-6 pulses for 30 s at 100 Watts (Hielscher ultrasonic processor, Germany), on ice. Soluble whole cell protein was collected by centrifugation at 12000 rpm at 4 • C for 10 min followed by passage through 0.2 μm syringe filter and stored at -80 • C until further application [CITATION_1] .",
